# Workspace Instructions

This workspace is focused on **automated BDD test case generation** from JIRA issues and **AI use case publishing** to Confluence using Cursor Agent rules.

## Rules

- **`@generate-test-cases`** — primary rule. Accepts a JIRA issue key (e.g. `PROJ-123`), a JIRA issue URL, or free-text acceptance criteria. Produces a prioritised Gherkin test suite saved as a Markdown file in `test-cases-output/`.
- **`@generate-jira-test-cases`** — primary rule. Accepts only a JIRA issue key or URL and generates a new markdown test suite in `test-cases-output/` for QA review.
- **`@publish-test-cases-to-testrail`** — primary rule. Accepts a reviewed markdown file path and publishes mapped test cases to TestRail.
- **`@create-ai-use-case`** — primary rule. Drafts an AI use case justification document from a Markdown file or plain text, shows a draft for approval, then publishes it as a new Confluence page.
- **`jira-auth`** — internal auth helper. Fetched automatically by the agent when JIRA credentials are needed. Do not invoke directly.
- **`confluence-auth`** — internal auth helper. Fetched automatically by the agent when Confluence credentials are needed. Do not invoke directly.
- **`testrail-auth`** — internal auth helper. Reads TestRail credentials from `.env` and prepares auth headers.
- **`transform-and-push-testrail`** — internal helper. Parses reviewed markdown test cases, maps to TestRail payloads, ensures section exists, and creates/updates cases.

## Behaviour guidelines

- Always read credentials from `.env` — never ask the user for them interactively.
- Never overwrite existing test case files — always create a new file per run.
- Never modify source code, configuration, or documentation files other than the generated test case Markdown and AI use case drafts.
- Use concrete, realistic test data in scenarios — no placeholders like `<email>`.
- Prioritise test cases P1 → P4; within each band order Positive → Negative → Edge.

## Folder conventions

| Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `.cursor/rules/` | Cursor rule files (`*.mdc`) |
| `.cursor/rules/prompts/` | Reusable prompt files |
| `.cursor/rules/instructions/` | Context-specific instruction files |
| `test-cases-output/` | Generated BDD test case Markdown files |
| `input-images/` | Optional screenshots for test case enrichment |
| `/memories/session/` | Session credential cache (auto-managed, do not edit manually) |
